data.value:
Hardware Accelerated Encoder
Encoders that utilize Hardware Acceleration (use hardware to Encode video steams) this option only accept Encoder name Ex: `h264_nvenc`(for NVIDIA), `h264_amf`(form AMD) for more info on Hardware Acceleration see Documents menu

data.name: label12.Text
data.value:
FFmpeg is a really powerful program that can do anything from recording screen Edit video, audio and even streaming all in one! while it may sounds convincing, using it can give some people a goosebumps.
since it's a command line application using it can be quite challenging, you can find your self getting nowhere in the swamp of text trying to figure out how to do just a simple stuff like trimming video or convert it to another format.
and this is where this program may came in handy, FFmpeg EZ (FFmpeg made easy) as the name suggest aims to make FFmpeg easier to use and understand for every one.
From someone who almost giving up I would regret not using it and wouldn't want to see people giving up on this powerful tool either.
I am no expert but like to share what little I know in the hopes that may be useful for someone.
